# Project Scope Statement

## Project Purpose
The purpose of this project is to design and publish a professional two-page website reviewing the recently released video game Marathon by Bungie. The website demonstrates foundational web development skills using HTML5 and CSS3 while presenting structured gaming analysis.

## Project Objectives
- Develop a functional two-page website with consistent navigation.
- Apply a single external CSS file for unified styling.
- Present organized review content including gameplay analysis and visuals.
- Deploy the website using GitHub Pages.
- Provide supporting project documentation.

## Deliverables
- index.html (homepage with review content)
- about.html (project and reviewer information)
- style.css (external stylesheet)
- Documentation folder including scope, plan, and retrospective
- Live website link hosted publicly

## In Scope
- Static HTML pages
- Responsive layout using basic CSS
- Screenshot gallery section
- Smooth scrolling and sticky navigation

## Out of Scope
- JavaScript interactivity
- User comments or login systems
- Backend functionality

## Constraints
- Limited to HTML and CSS only
- Academic timeline
- Single stylesheet requirement

## Assumptions
- Users will access the site on modern browsers.
- Official game promotional materials are publicly accessible.